Leanna Blemker
March 31, 2018 at 4:05 PM ¬∑

Only 6-1/2 months after receiving a diagnosis of ALS, my best friend passed away. Visitation will be at Nass and Son funeral home, Huntingburg, on Saturday, April 7th from 2-8 pm (Eastern time). Private funeral services for the family will be held at another time. In lieu of flowers, memorial contributions may be made to Huntingburg United Methodist Church for youth programing or outreach programing.

NewsNow Dubois County
November 18, 2017 at 10:17 AM ¬∑

RAIDERS PLAY TODAY FOR TRIP TO STATE

The Southridge Raiders, who rolled over Providence, 47-7, November 10 to win the IHSAA Class 2A Regional at Raider Field in Huntingburg, are playing Indianapolis Scecina Memorial this afternoon in the 2A Semistate at Indianapolis Tech. Kickoff at 2 p.m. The winner advances to next week's 2A state championship game.

Coach Scott Buening‚Äôs Raiders take an 11-2 record and a 4-game winning streak into the game, having won 10 of their last 11 games. Scecina‚Äôs Crusaders, who defeated Western Boone, 48-33, in their regional final, take a 12-1 record and an 8-game winning streak into the game. Their lone defeat was 38-7 to Indianapolis Roncalli back on September 15.

Because of exclusive rights with the IHSAA the game will not air on NewsNow Dubois County. It will be streamed live at www.ihsaatv.org.

Hannah Thyen, a former SHS classmate who co-owns The Doodlebug craft store in Jasper, set up the account after talking with other members of the Southridge class of 1996.

Humorists Scott Saalman, Abbie Rumbach, and Gene Baldwin along with musicians Billie & Buddy Hart, Ed Walston, Kasha Schwartz Phillips, Rob Zaricki, and Danielle Lee & the Sisters of Second Avenue will read (and sing) to benefit TRI-CAP.
